## Import Order

**The principle:** Imports are ordered by distance from the current file - furthest away first, closest last. Separate each group with a blank line.

[REFERENCE] Common implementation:

```
1. Language / framework built-ins (furthest - part of the platform)
2. External packages (third-party libraries)
3. Internal absolute imports (your project's own code via aliases)
4. Relative imports (siblings, parents - closest to the current file)
5. Side-effect-only imports (styles, polyfills, or anything with no named import - if your stack has them)
```

Some stacks have additional groups (type-only imports, protocol imports, generated code). Add them where they logically fit in the "distance from current file" ordering and be consistent.

**Sort within each group:** Alphabetically by package/module name.

